parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities
head striking the windshield
burns from airbag deployment
and vehicle damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause injuries, distractions, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: Airbags deploy unexpectedly
resulting in bruises
injuries
and vehicle damage
often due to minor incidents such as hitting a bump or railroad tracks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning airbag sensors can cause airbags to fail to deploy or deploy unexpectedly, leading to injuries or accidents.
symptoms: Airbag sensors are damaged or malfunctioning
causing airbags to deploy unnecessarily or fail to deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of an airbag on/off switch can be a concern for some drivers, particularly those who may need to adjust their seating position for better visibility.
symptoms: Request for an airbag on/off switch to be installed in the vehicle
citing concerns about airbag deployment and seating position.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Failure to Engage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or failure to engage can cause the vehicle to lurch forward or decelerate suddenly, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission randomly slams into a lower gear
gets stuck in a gear
fails to go into overdrive
lugs back and then goes forward
will not shift gears
downshifts on its own
and may cause the vehicle to jerk or lurch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to diagnose transmission problems can lead to prolonged periods of unsafe driving conditions, as the root cause of the issue remains unknown.
symptoms: Difficulty diagnosing the transmission problem without an engine code
despite attempts to repair or replace components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of transmission components can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The need to replace transmission components
such as the computer
or reset the computer to resolve transmission issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to seize, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates
the steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel seizes or locks up
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause injuries to occupants, damage to the vehicle, and potentially lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without any impact or crash
occupants experience bruising or other injuries
windshield shattered by airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering and alignment system can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the steering wheel feels uneven or crooked
the vehicle is difficult to hold steady while turning
bent wheels or uneven tire wear.
